	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>A reminder that Spirit as it stands sucks for almost everybody except healbot Priests and shape-shifting Druids.  It CAN kick in and provide SOME help for Warlocks (though they have other ways to recoup mana) and the mana-using melee classes (Hunter, Shaman, Paladin), since they can contribute to a fight without casting, but they'll WANT to be casting frequently to maximize their input whenever possible.  Healbot priests and shape-shifting Druids are reactive casters, who want to preserve mana and cast only when needed, giving time for spirit to matter.<br />
<br />
So the catch is making Spirit useful for people who get almost nothing from it now (with Mages probably being the chief example, followed by the hybrids and Warlocks) without beefing up the restorative classes who already get some utility from it.  The idea of any sort of sustainable regeneration in combat rather bothers me (for both healing and mana), since it will ultimately lead to really long, drawn out fights...<br />
<br />
Mage Armor is the first target, and we'll see how it goes.  As I mentioned, though, I don't think it will be substantial.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
