	</tr>
	</table>
</div>No.  I *have* tried going all out spirit with my Mage, and I feel qualified to comment on it.<br />
<br />
There are a couple of reasons it's not very useful:<br />
<br />
1) About the only way to get high Spirit is to give up Stamina, and giving up stamina makes us dead.  My Mage at 53 has 2700 HP, and there are times I need every last point.  We AE, and when we AE we get hit - I'd really rather be alive.<br />
<br />
2) All we can do if we aren't casting is shoot our wand or melee.  Neither of them contribute much (I'm aware that healer Priests find these things acceptable, but since they're not there to do damage pretty much ANYTHING they contribute is good - as a damage dealer, doing maybe 15% of my spell-based DPS is not really acceptable).<br />
<br />
3) Water.  We can always sit out a fight and keep drinking if needed.<br />
<br />
4) Evocation &amp; Conjured Mana Stone.  If we really need the extra juice and haven't had a chance to rest, we can bust out another full mana bar in about 8 seconds.  Spirit can impact Evocation, but since you'll HOLD less mana with a spirit build, RESTORING more mana will do you no good.<br />
<br />
All of that combined makes spirit suck for us.  It's pretty much a non-combat ability, and the only time it even kicks in really is when you're running somewhere between fights.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
