	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>Quinalla</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">Spirit does work, but you have to remember the 5-second rule and getting talents that allow you to regen a percentage of mana while casting and during the 5-seconds helps a lot.  Priests, mages and druids all have a talent that does this.  My spirit is 280 right now unbuffed (and my int is 330, so int isn't suffering from trying to get spirit) and it and my talent help me a ton in fights.  Often at the end of a long fight when everyone is oom or low, I am able to regen enough to cast a heal when needed, I couldn't do that without spirit.  I do still run oom, but I know I will regen it quickly and innervate is a beautiful spell with lots of spirit <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smilie" class="inlineimg" /><br />
<br />
I think a lot of mages don't get spirit gear because as they level solo and in instance groups, they nearly chain cast spells during the battle and then drink between every or every other fight.  Priests don't typically chain cast in "normal" battles and if heals are timed well, they can get some ticks of regen even without talents.  I know when I group with a mage, they often stop to drink when my mana is still pretty high, even on pulls where I am putting dots on mobs and throwing an occasional nuke.<br />
<br />
Does anyone know mages that focus more on spi?  I don't know any and I would be curious to see how it works for them.<br />
<br />
And yeah, I don't usually worry about warlocks and spirit since their hp bar is another mana bar for them.  Int/Sta are the primary stats for warlocks, but for mages, Spi seems like it should be more important than Sta, but it isn't for any mage I have met yet.</div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div><br />
<br />
<br />
Well from a pvp server perspective Sta is the second most important stan after Int EASILY for a mage.  The amount of spirit that you would have to have to have any noticeable difference be seen is just not worth it in almost any fight.  The only time fights last long enough for mana regen to ever even truely become a factor is in Molten Core/Onyxia or perhaps taking out a opposing faction boss.<br />
<br />
Spirt does have some effect, but not at all enough currently to make giving up survival which stamina is.  Dreadmist vs Magister debate is about survival not about spirit.  Since they have nearly identical spirit.  I personally at this point would see absolutely no benefit in being a "spirit" mage.  You would die so easily that who cares if you can regen 1 percent faster.<br />
<br />
This is also going to be key in the use of Mage Armor as a whole anyway.  If it does not stack with ice Armor.  Is it going to be worth it to not have Ice armor which is a great defensive buff in PVP and PVE for the X amount of regen/resists mage armor will provide.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
